JS is programming language
-->used to make the static webpages as dynamic
-->It is often used in client side validartion
-->JS versions will be referred as ES versions
-->latest ES9. Most commonly used version is ES6
--> ES-EMCAScript
-->JS is an interpreter software[scans code line by line]
-->It is a loosely-coupled  language[datatpe can be modified
                                eg:- int a =10; 
                                     a = "Hello";//Type mismatch will not occur]

Ways to work with JS
1. INternal scripting --> Inside the same document using script tag 
2. External scripting --> Separate JS file and connecting it with 
                          current HTML file using <script src="filePath"/>

Dispaly the outputs in JS
1. alert("Message"); --> dialog box
2. document.write("Message"); --> new page
3. document.getElementById("idName").innerHTML = "Message"; -->same page
4. console.log("Message); --> console Window

JS comments
1. Single line comment --> //
2. Mulitline comment --> /* */

JS variables
Syntax
keyword varName = value

JS keywords for creating variables
1. var --> Global --> accessible throughtout the scripting
2. Let --> Local --> accessible only within the block
3. const --> constant --> cannot be modified

JS datatypes
1. String --> includes character --> denoted as '' or "" or ``[Template literals]
2. Number --> includes whole and decimal Number
3. Boolean --> true or false
4. null --> Empty [valid value]
5. undefined --> It means the value is not inintialized yet.

